Get or set the current active kubectx
If no args are provided, the current context is retrieved. 
If a target argument is provided, then stack will activate the configured context for the environment with name matching target.

Usage:
  stack context [target] [flags]
  stack context [command]

Available Commands:
  list        A brief description of your command

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for context

Global Flags:
  -r, --project_directory string     set the project directory of the stack (default ".")
      --stack_configuration string   set the name of the configuration file to be used (default ".stack-local")

Use "stack context [command] --help" for more information about a command.
